1772630576861322	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3kws		item.create	bn-kfc4	{"description":"## Problem\n\n`ensure_projection` uses a one-directional staleness check:\n\n```rust\ntotal_bytes > cursor  // only catches: new events added after last build\n```\n\nThis misses the inverse case: **cursor > total_bytes** — which happens after cross-machine sync where the local shard sequence is shorter than what the DB was built against. The DB looks \"current\" (cursor >= total_bytes) but is actually stale or wrong for this machine's event history.\n\n## Concrete scenario\n\n1. Machine A has shards: 2026-01.events (500KB) + 2026-03.events (300KB) → cursor = 800KB, DB has 133 items\n2. DB is copied/synced to Machine B, which only has 2026-03.events (300KB)\n3. On Machine B: total_bytes = 300KB, cursor = 800KB → `300 > 800` is false → no rebuild triggered\n4. Machine B uses the DB as-is — it may have items whose events aren't in the local shards, and may be missing items whose events are only in the local shards\n\n## Fix\n\nIn `ensure_projection` (db/mod.rs), treat cursor > total_bytes as a staleness signal requiring a full rebuild:\n\n```rust\nlet needs_rebuild = ... {\n    ...\n    } else {\n        let mgr = crate::shard::ShardManager::new(bones_dir);\n        let total_bytes = mgr.total_content_len().unwrap_or(0);\n        let cursor = usize::try_from(offset).unwrap_or(0);\n        // Stale if new events exist OR if cursor overshoots local shards\n        // (the latter happens after sync when shard history differs)\n        total_bytes != cursor\n    }\n};\n```\n\nUsing `!=` instead of `>` catches both directions. A full rebuild is the right response in either case since the shard sequence has changed.\n\n## Observed symptom\n\n`bn triage graph` showed bones in the dependency graph (referenced by dep edges in the event log) that had no title or data — they existed as edge endpoints but not as projectable items, because the local DB was built from a different machine's shard history and was missing 83 of 133 bones. `bn admin rebuild` fixed it by ignoring the cursor and replaying all local events.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `ws/default/crates/bones-core/src/db/mod.rs`: `ensure_projection()` staleness check\n- Consider also logging a warning when cursor > total_bytes so the mismatch is visible","kind":"task","title":"ensure_projection should rebuild when cursor exceeds total shard bytes"}	blake3:cpgz8BOWaSgVVbCUT7jVVq65ejGBB0oIVOzMau8Shfw
1772631035846885	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3lAs		item.move	bn-kfc4	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:abRKEz_iljfgpmpZIHinMWq2AYoUxFNrRkdaXZrpI9o
