1773604881477330	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3yQs		item.comment	bn-blv7	{"body":"## Investigation Results: No memory leak found\n\n### Methodology\n\n**Phase 1: Isolated path benchmarks** (cargo bench harnesses)\nExercised each allocation-heavy TUI path in isolation with 500+ iterations, measuring RSS via /proc/self/statm:\n\n| Path | Iterations | RSS Growth |\n|------|-----------|------------|\n| reload (list_items + get_labels, 750 items) | 500 | 1.0 MB then flat |\n| load_detail_item (15 comments) | 500 | 0.0 MB |\n| detail_lines markdown render | 5000 | 0.0 MB |\n| ratatui Terminal::draw + Paragraph.wrap | 50,000 frames | 0.4 MB then flat |\n| ORT semantic model + inference | 5000 inferences | 65 MB load + 6.5 MB then flat |\n| Full tick cycle (all combined) | 500 | 0.0 MB |\n\nScaled to 200 comments/item (150K total): RSS stable at 5.3 MB.\n\n**Phase 2: Real TUI soak via vessel**\nSpawned `bn ui` in vessel, sent real keypresses via `vessel send-keys`, monitored RSS via `vessel list --format json`:\n\nTest 1 — Navigation soak (ward, 755 items): 120s, 22 action cycles → 68.8 MB → 68.8 MB (0.0 MB growth)\n\nTest 2 — ORT search soak (ward): 20 search queries → 68.6 MB → 73.8 MB (+5.1 MB one-time ORT warmup, then flat)\n\nTest 3 — Full stress test (demo project, ~220 items):\n- 60 bones created externally while TUI open\n- 10 comments added externally\n- 12 semantic search queries\n- 4 shift+D done toggles\n- 10 rapid navigation cycles with detail pane\n- Result: 68.3 MB → 73.4 MB (+5.1 MB ORT warmup, then flat across all actions)\n\n### Conclusion\n\nNo memory leak exists in `bn ui`. RSS is stable across all tested paths including external mutations, search, done toggling, and rapid navigation. The reported 1.6 GB was likely environmental (other process, swap pressure, stale WAL under heavy concurrent agent writes, or misattribution).\n\n### Fixes shipped anyway (performance, not leak)\n- Cached detail_lines() (eliminates ~21 redundant Vec<Line> allocs/sec)\n- Staleness check skips SQLite reload when bone unchanged\n- Comment cap at 200 in detail pane\n- dhat-heap and jemalloc feature flags for future profiling\n- Benchmark harnesses (tui_memory, tui_render_memory, tui_ort_memory)\n- Soak test script (crates/bones-cli/benches/tui_soak.sh)"}	blake3:0o3VYxL7YC7qIIEHe1WjIlkNR46_yAbad0SZGpBqj2s
1773604887198288	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3ygs		item.move	bn-blv7	{"state":"done"}	blake3:eEv2H6rhwkwwJAtHm7Bn3eGAQ16IKNKpUZ97mnsw4cM
